title: Ibrar Ahmed wins NA-55 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan Muslim League-Nawaz’s (PML-N) Ibrar Ahmed has won the election for National Assembly constituency NA-55 Rawalpindi-IV by securing 78,542 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was independent candidate Muhammad Basharat Raja, who bagged 67,101 votes.
The overall voters’ turnout remained 39.99 percent.
